<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Cuba:  draft decision 
</b></p>
<p><b>2006/&#8230; The use of mercenaries as a means of violating human rights and 
impeding the exercise of the right of peoples to self-determination 
</b></p>
<p> The Human Rights Council, recalling resolution 2005/2 of 7 April 2005 of the 
Commission on Human Rights and taking note of the report of the Working Group on the use of 
mercenaries as a means of violating human rights and impeding the exercise of the right of 
peoples to self-determination (E/CN.4/2006/11), decides: 
</p>
<p> (<i>a</i>) To authorize the Working Group to hold three sessions per year; 
</p>
<p> (<i>b</i>) To request the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights to convene 
a high-level round table to discuss the fundamental question of the role of the State as the 
primary holder of the monopoly on the use of force, with the objective of facilitating a critical 
understanding as to the responsibilities of different actors in the current context, including 
private military and security companies, and their respective obligations for the protection and 
promotion of human rights. 
</p>
